Azure.Monitor.OpenTelemetry.AspNetCore 1.4.0

### Describe the bug

In my asp.net core 10 app I have SignalR and OTel setup.
For auth reasons and browser limitations my FE has to send access_token in url (as query param) in upgrade to WS request. When I use OTel ConsoleExporter or OtlpExporter everything is good, because access_token is redacted from spans attributes (I see that in console and in jaeger which I connect using OtlpExporter). But when I start use UseAzureMonitor it seems somehow affects this behavior and `access_token` query param is not redacted anymore.

Libs:
Azure.Monitor.OpenTelemetry.Profiler 1.0.0-beta5
Azure.Monitor.OpenTelemetry.AspNetCore 1.4.0
OpenTelemetry 1.15.0
OpenTelemetry.Exporter.Console 1.15.0
OpenTelemetry.Exporter.OpenTelemetryProtocol 1.15.0
OpenTelemetry.Extensions.Hosting 1.15.0
OpenTelemetry.Instrumentation.AspNetCore 1.15.0
OpenTelemetry.Instrumentation.EventCounters 1.5.1-alpha.1
OpenTelemetry.Instrumentation.Http 1.15.0
OpenTelemetry.Instrumentation.Runtime 1.15.0
OpenTelemetry.Instrumentation.SqlClient 1.15.0


### Expected behavior

I expect to see redacted access_token from url. 

<img width="591" height="422" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c83c4fe0-b7d3-4854-a946-e952db1ae34b" />

### Actual behavior

<img width="756" height="442" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/84f5c06a-c94d-4312-8aba-e8a0151cb6e4" />

### Reproduction Steps

```c#
public static IServiceCollection AddTelemetry(this IServiceCollection services, IConfiguration configuration)
    {
        var options = new TelemetryOptions();
        configuration.GetSection("Telemetry").Bind(options);

        services
            .AddLogging()
            .AddOpenTelemetry()
            .ConfigureResource(e => e.AddService(SERVICE_NAME))
            .WithTracing(tracing =>
            {
                tracing
                    .AddSqlClientInstrumentation()
                    .AddHttpClientInstrumentation()
                    .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation();
            })
            .WithMetrics(metrics =>
            {
                metrics
                    .AddSqlClientInstrumentation()
                    .AddEventCountersInstrumentation(e =>
                    {
                        e.RefreshIntervalSecs = 5;
                    })
                    .AddRuntimeInstrumentation()
                    .AddHttpClientInstrumentation()
                    .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation();
            })
            .WithLogging();

        services
            .AddExporters(options);

        return services;
    }

    private static IServiceCollection AddExporters(this IServiceCollection services, TelemetryOptions options)
    {
        if (options.Exporters.AzureMonitor != null)
        {
            var exporter = options.Exporters.AzureMonitor;

            services
                .AddOpenTelemetry()
                .UseAzureMonitor(e => { e.ConnectionString = exporter.ConnectionString; })
                .AddAzureMonitorProfiler();
        }

        if (options.Exporters.Otlp != null)
        {
            var exporter = options.Exporters.Otlp;

            services
                .AddOpenTelemetry()
                .UseOtlpExporter(exporter.Protocol, exporter.BaseUrl);
        }

        if (options.Exporters.Console != null)
        {
            var exporter = options.Exporters.Console;

            services
                .AddOpenTelemetry()
                .WithTracing(e =>
                {
                    if (exporter.Tracing) e.AddConsoleExporter();
                })
                .WithMetrics(e =>
                {
                    if (exporter.Metrics) e.AddConsoleExporter();
                })
                .WithLogging(e =>
                {
                    if (exporter.Logging) e.AddConsoleExporter();
                });
        }

        return services;
    }
```

